New Mexico has lived for too long under failed Republican leadership with Gov. Martinez. And the tea partier who’s running to replace her, Steve Pearce, would be even worse – he even has Trump’s “full support!” I’m running for Governor to turn New Mexico blue and invest in our state’s future, but I need to know where 5,000 people stand before this poll closes at the end of this week: Do you approve of Gov. Martinez?

TIME-SENSITIVE POLL: Do you approve of Gov. Martinez?
I need 5,000 responses but yours is missing! Tell me ASAP: Do you approve of Gov. Martinez?

Suggested Post
Soi Dog Foundation
Sp
S
on
S
so
S
red
S
 ·

This is Bowie. He now lives in a wonderful home in the UK but he has been through hell to get there.

Bowie was abandoned in the streets of Thailand, where he had burning oil thrown over him. This horrific act went unpunished, in a country with weak animal welfare laws. Please demand change! Sign the petition now to demand justice for animals like Bowie: https://bit.ly/Justice_For_Dogs_Like_Bowie

In late December 2014, Thailand introduced its first animal welfare law. Prior t...o this, acts of animal cruelty were not considered a criminal offence. The new law changed this, introducing maximum penalties of up to 2 years’ imprisonment and/or a 40,000 THB fine (approximately US$1,200).

But to this day, sentencing in animal abuse cases continues to be shockingly lenient, meaning there is no adequate deterrent in place. Until the sentencing reflects the serious nature of the crime, incidences of horrific animal cruelty will continue. Please sign the petition now and demand justice for dogs like Bowie, the innocent victims of shocking cruelty and abuse: https://bit.ly/Justice_For_Dogs_Like_Bowie

Following treatment at Soi Dog Foundation, Bowie made a wonderful recovery and was adopted to a loving home in the UK. But we are determined to get justice for victims of animal abuse like him. Please sign the petition now, demanding that acts of animal abuse in Thailand be punished to the full extent of the law: https://bit.ly/Justice_For_Dogs_Like_Bowie

See More
Punish Animal Cruelty Offences In Thailand To The Full Extent Of The Law!
Please ask Thailand's Minister of Justice to show the world that his country stands with other civilised countries in not tolerating cruelty to sentient beings.
soidog.org
